ESSENTIAL LINUX COMMANDS TO CREATE FILES AND DIRECTORY
    touch : creates empty files
    touch { numbers } : this creates multiple files in one command example for this would be [ (touch bootcamp{1,2,3}.txt) output (bootcamp1.txt, bootcamp2.txt, bootcamp3.txt) ] for a large range you would ( touch test{1..50}) soo dot dot instead of commars.
    echo : out puts line of text in a file and creates the file if it doesnt already exist 
    printf :  out puts line of text in a file and creates the file if it doesnt already exists ( the same thing as echo )
    vim : is a file text editor, creates file for you and also opens up an editor which allows you edit the file by pressing 'i' and saving it by quitting and using 'wq!'.
    mkdir: creates directorys e.g. [ mkdir directory ] and to create mulitple you could also use [mkir directory {1..50}] createing directories 1-50.

